43: The Hive.text_posted:
@Fert12334
That's because this is a 'Mono Artifact' (Look at it's type line). 'Mono' was an old subtype of artifact that inherently required a [T] to use it's ability, so it only had one use per turn (hence the 'Mono'.) Sort of like how the land subtype 'Forest' inherently adds "[T]: Add [G] to your mana pool." to what ever [autocard multiverseid="249389"]land[/autocard] it's on. 

The alternative was 'Poly Artifact' that did not need the [T] and so could be activated multiple times a turn. [autocard]Pyramids[/autocard] being one of these. And other was 'Continuous Artifact' that needed no activation, but had static or triggered abilities, like Enchantments. One you should be familiar with is [autocard]Howling Mine[/autocard], which only recently left Standard. The line on the Mine about only if is untapped on the more recent versions is also something that was part of the Continuous line of artifacts, in that they lost their effect when tapped.

